This paper presents a visual servoing approach for a robot arm, which involves using multiple cameras to track a moving target in the presence of occlusions. This topic is highly relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for object tracking. The approach also involves using a master supervisor task to select the best camera input, which could involve machine learning or decision-making algorithms (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the approach involves controlling the robot arm, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
